    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="718"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10498</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Greek Legation</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Greek Minister<note n="7" xml:id="d718fn7">Cimon P. Diamantopoulos.</note> is
                    instructed to suggest to the United States Government that it would be of high
                    importance to issue a declaration <pb facs="0737" n="725" xml:id="pg_725"/>
                    stating that no forcible territorial modifications at the expense of the
                    integrity of Greece shall be recognized. The Greek Government think that it
                    would be, moreover, advisable to warn the Bulgarian Government on the sanctions
                    to be taken in case where any methods (transfer of populations) would be applied
                    in order to alter the ethnological complexion of Thrace and Macedonia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-24">April 24,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
